  "title": "Nursing Aide",
  "description": "<p>Position: Nursing Aide\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p><p>Reports to: Senior Staff Nurse / Senior Nurse Manager</p><p>Job Description</p><p>- Attends to residents’ needs</p><p>- Makes rounds to check residents’ condition regularly.</p><p>- Performed basic nursing duties such as: </p><ul><li>nasogastric feeding</li></ul><ul><li>bathing and toileting</li></ul><ul><li>wound dressing</li></ul><ul><li>blood glucose monitoring</li></ul><p>vital signs, such as: </p><ul><li>temperature, blood pressure, pulse rate, respiration rate, pain score and oxygen saturation.</li></ul><p>- Reports above to staff nurse accordingly.</p><p>- Assists staff nurse writing resident’s reports and documentation of resident’s vital signs and other charts.</p><p>- Supervises health care assistants.</p><p>- Makes and tidies beds with health care assistants.</p><p>- Assist residents in their activities of daily living (ADL), e.g. bathing, oral hygiene, dressing up, grooming.</p><p>- Attends monthly In-house training programmes, so as to update and upgrade own knowledge and skills.</p><p>- Attends monthly clinical staff meetings, so as to be updated on the latest happenings in the Nursing Home/</p><p>- Assists staff nurse to prepare Residents’ reports for Multidisciplinary Rounds presentation every 6 monthly.</p><p>-  Mentors newly employed NAs for 3 months, as and whenever assigned by the Nurse Manager and/or Director <br />of Nursing.</p><p>Qualifications/Experience</p><p>1) Basic Cardiac Life Support Certification License.</p><p>2) Diploma or Degree in Nursing (for Foreign Nurses)</p><p>3) Some experience in a nursing home in a similar position.</p><p>4) Ability to communicate at all levels.</p>",
